</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujochangaladar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 335<br> <font color=#333333>(6/14/02 3:23:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=97.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Improved Reclaim Energy Fixed</span><hr size=1>     My assumption on how Improved Reclaim (which of course is only an assumption) is that you will not get 100% of the casting cost back by reclaiming your pet.  Specialize, SCM, and Summoning Efficiency effectively overbalance this, and you should gain mana when you reclaim.  My assumption for illustration purposes is 90%, but I could easily be off.<br>
<br>
    Someone mentioned that the best they could do with Spell Casting Mastery 3, Quick Summoning 3, and Improved reclaim was roughly 40 mana per tic (approx equivalent to meditate rate + Clarity2), which is roughly 60 mana per reclaim.  If SCM 3 is 25% mana savings, and Improved Reclaim is 90% of the casting cost, then the net gain is 15% of the mana cost (use the 57 earth as an example, 400 mana).  This would equate to 60 mana per reclaim as was observed.<br>
<br>
    How will it work with the epic pet?  Ideally, it should give back somewhere around 90% of the 500 mana casting cost of the Orb....  assuming they really fixed epic pet reclaim. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showMessageRange?topicID=97.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showPrevMessage?topicID=97.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showNextMessage?topicID=97.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=97.topic&index=29><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.threadControl?topicID=97.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=97.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=97.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="